If you’re using PHP 5.5+, this should be all you need to securely save passwords:<p><pre><code>  $sHash = password_hash(&#x27;ThePassword&#x27;, PASSWORD_BCRYPT, [&#x27;cost&#x27; => 12]);
</code></pre>
Checking is as easily as:<p><pre><code>  if (password_verify(&#x27;ThePassword&#x27;, $sHash)) {…}
</code></pre>
Or do you guys have other thoughts?
